6️⃣ Edge Case Questions
❓ “How would you handle false positives?”
Correct answer:
“I would not permanently lock account on first anomaly.
Instead apply step-up authentication and allow recovery path.”
This shows product understanding.

❓ “How do you protect against distributed credential stuffing?”
Strong answer:
“Per-account rate limiting is more effective than per-IP.
I would throttle login attempts per user ID regardless of source IP.”

❓ “Is storing JWT in localStorage safe?”
Correct:
“No. If XSS exists, attacker can steal it.
Prefer HttpOnly cookie with CSRF protection.”

❓ “How would you secure mobile login?”
	• Certificate pinning
	• Device binding
	• Secure keystore storage
	• App attestation
